1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,750
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:03,550 --> 00:00:05,583
(Hanyang Fresh Makgeolli)

4
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:08,883
I think I'm going to give up.

5
00:00:10,450 --> 00:00:12,050
What, dieting?

6
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:15,250
Have you even been listening?

7
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:19,483
I really don't understand my feelings.

8
00:00:20,450 --> 00:00:22,283
When I think about him,

9
00:00:22,450 --> 00:00:24,950
my heart feels all warm...

10
00:00:25,583 --> 00:00:26,583
and tingly.

11
00:00:28,150 --> 00:00:31,583
And still, you're giving up...

12
00:00:31,583 --> 00:00:33,550
because that Manager Seo or whoever
liked him first?

13
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:36,850
Is love first-come, first-served?

14
00:00:37,150 --> 00:00:39,850
If that's the case,
you were first. 25 years ago.

15
00:00:39,850 --> 00:00:41,583
I was only five.

16
00:00:42,350 --> 00:00:44,083
And my team manager...

17
00:00:44,350 --> 00:00:47,650
is going back to the U.S.
after this project.

18
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:51,450
You think you're being cool right now,
don't you?

19
00:00:51,783 --> 00:00:54,350
Is it cool to give up
before even starting?

20
00:00:54,483 --> 00:00:57,550
Then what do you want me to do? Confess?

21
00:00:57,950 --> 00:01:00,950
No, I can't. I won't.

22
00:01:03,750 --> 00:01:05,450
I do have an idea, though.

23
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:07,283
You're drunk.

24
00:01:08,150 --> 00:01:10,550
Go to him like this...

25
00:01:10,950 --> 00:01:12,983
Go to him and?

26
00:01:14,383 --> 00:01:15,383
Make a move.

27
00:01:15,650 --> 00:01:17,150
What? Make a...

28
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:21,950
What? She passed out.

29
00:01:22,450 --> 00:01:23,983
What should I do? Eun Ae?

30
00:01:31,083 --> 00:01:32,350
I'm back.

31
00:01:58,383 --> 00:02:00,250
The familiar smell of my room.

32
00:02:02,483 --> 00:02:03,950
Did I drink too much makgeolli?

33
00:02:11,250 --> 00:02:12,350
So tiring.

34
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:19,883
Hurry and wash up.

35
00:02:19,883 --> 00:02:21,050
I'll get breakfast ready. It'll be quick.

36
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:23,050
Is Eun Ae not up yet?

37
00:02:27,683 --> 00:02:28,750
What was that?

38
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:29,783
It sounded like Eun Ae.

39
00:02:33,983 --> 00:02:36,650
What? Team Manager, why are you here?

40
00:02:36,883 --> 00:02:39,250
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, why are you in my room?

41
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:42,783
Your room?
This is my house. Are you dreaming?

42
00:02:42,783 --> 00:02:45,483
What? This is your house?

43
00:02:45,983 --> 00:02:48,050
- I moved in here yesterday as a tenant.
- What?

44
00:02:52,283 --> 00:02:53,650
What's going on?

45
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:56,350
- What was that?
- Eun Ae!

46
00:02:56,483 --> 00:02:57,550
- You jerk!
- Eun Ae!

47
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,783
Eun Ae, are you okay?

48
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:07,450
You jerk, what did you do to my daughter?

49
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:08,450
Wait!

50
00:03:09,150 --> 00:03:11,550
What's wrong with you all?
Nothing happened.

51
00:03:11,850 --> 00:03:13,483
I think there's been
some misunderstanding.

52
00:03:13,483 --> 00:03:15,250
Everyone, calm down, okay? Calm down.

53
00:03:15,950 --> 00:03:16,983
Actually...

54
00:03:17,550 --> 00:03:19,850
I was so drunk yesterday
that I got the rooms mixed up.

55
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,750
I mean, this used to be my room, right?

56
00:03:23,383 --> 00:03:26,183
What's with you? Let me speak too.

57
00:03:26,183 --> 00:03:27,550
I swear, this jerk!

58
00:03:29,650 --> 00:03:30,850
Team Manager Ko?

59
00:03:31,683 --> 00:03:32,683
Mr. Cho.

60
00:03:33,083 --> 00:03:35,450
Why? Do you know him?

61
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:39,750
He's my team manager.

62
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:41,350
Team Manager?

63
00:03:42,250 --> 00:03:44,350
So you didn't know
this was Eun Ae's house...

64
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:46,350
when you rented the place,

65
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:48,250
and Eun Ae, you were drunk...

66
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:50,950
and reflexively went into your old room,

67
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:52,783
so you ended up sleeping together
in the same room?

68
00:03:52,783 --> 00:03:54,483
Yes, that's right.

69
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:56,150
We did sleep...

70
00:03:56,683 --> 00:03:58,583
I mean, it seems like we did.

71
00:03:59,383 --> 00:04:02,150
But please don't get the wrong idea.

72
00:04:02,150 --> 00:04:03,383
Yes, that's correct.

73
00:04:03,650 --> 00:04:05,150
Until I woke up just now,

74
00:04:05,150 --> 00:04:07,250
I slept so soundly
I didn't even realize...

75
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:08,650
someone was lying next to me.

76
00:04:08,850 --> 00:04:10,650
I'm glad you slept well.

77
00:04:10,983 --> 00:04:13,450
But why did you come here
instead of staying at your own place?

78
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:14,483
It's even farther from the office.

79
00:04:14,883 --> 00:04:16,550
There are several reasons, but...

80
00:04:16,883 --> 00:04:19,750
Please speak casually.
We're not at the office.

81
00:04:19,883 --> 00:04:21,250
Well, we can get to that later.

82
00:04:21,683 --> 00:04:24,850
More importantly,
does your family know you moved here?

83
00:04:25,050 --> 00:04:29,150
No.
Please keep it a secret from my father.

84
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:30,750
Why?

85
00:04:31,083 --> 00:04:33,683
It's a long story,
but I'd really appreciate it.

86
00:04:34,550 --> 00:04:36,750
But are you sure you really didn't know...

87
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,350
whose house this was?

88
00:04:38,483 --> 00:04:40,450
What? Of course not.

89
00:04:40,683 --> 00:04:43,150
I knew it was Ms. Cho's neighborhood,
but still...

90
00:04:44,383 --> 00:04:45,683
Everyone has to go to work.

91
00:04:46,350 --> 00:04:48,383
Let's talk later. Go get ready.

92
00:04:48,550 --> 00:04:50,050
I'll set the table.
You eat too, Team Manager.

93
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:52,650
No, it's fine.
I'll just head straight to work.

94
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:55,450
What are you talking about?
You must've gone to bed hungry last night.

95
00:04:56,150 --> 00:04:57,150
I'll help too.

96
00:04:57,350 --> 00:04:58,983
You know
where the second-floor bathroom is, right?

97
00:04:58,983 --> 00:05:00,750
- Hurry up.
- Yes, okay.

98
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:04,450
Wait, we need to talk.

99
00:05:04,450 --> 00:05:05,950
What? Why? We're running late.

100
00:05:07,383 --> 00:05:08,383
What is it?

101
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,450
What are you saying?

102
00:05:12,650 --> 00:05:15,783
What do you think? Move out immediately.

103
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,750
Why should I?

104
00:05:17,950 --> 00:05:19,350
I just moved in yesterday,

105
00:05:19,350 --> 00:05:22,050
and I already paid the deposit
and a month's rent in advance.

106
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:25,050
You can just ask for it back.

107
00:05:26,050 --> 00:05:27,450
Why should I do that?

108
00:05:27,550 --> 00:05:29,983
So you're saying you're going to live
in the same house as me?

109
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:31,950
What if people at work find out?

110
00:05:32,150 --> 00:05:33,150
So what if they do?

111
00:05:33,350 --> 00:05:35,350
They're already having misunderstandings.

112
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:37,950
If they hear we live together,
you know what they'll say.

113
00:05:38,750 --> 00:05:40,550
"You know?" Know what?

114
00:05:40,950 --> 00:05:42,450
What is it?

115
00:05:47,383 --> 00:05:49,450
Grandma, what brings you here
so early in the morning?

116
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,750
This hangover soup.

117
00:05:50,883 --> 00:05:52,650
You drank all night with Cho Rong,

118
00:05:52,650 --> 00:05:54,950
so your stomach must be a mess.

119
00:05:55,550 --> 00:05:58,050
That team manager or whatever...

120
00:05:58,050 --> 00:06:00,450
"Just thinking about him
makes my heart warm"...

121
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:02,650
You were dreaming again, weren't you?

122
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:03,750
I'll enjoy this, Grandma.

123
00:06:03,850 --> 00:06:07,250
What was it? Warm, tingly...

124
00:06:08,050 --> 00:06:09,383
Grandma, you should get going...

125
00:06:09,383 --> 00:06:10,850
if you're going to make hangover soup
for Cho Rong too.

126
00:06:11,150 --> 00:06:13,450
Okay, don't push me. I'm going.

127
00:06:13,983 --> 00:06:16,050
But who's that? Eun Hyeong?

128
00:06:16,783 --> 00:06:17,883
Yes.

129
00:06:17,883 --> 00:06:19,883
Why is my brother over there?
I'll wake him up.

130
00:06:19,883 --> 00:06:21,550
- Goodbye!
- Bye.

131
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:26,350
Why do you keep putting things over me?
It's suffocating.

132
00:06:26,683 --> 00:06:29,450
I said move out right now!

133
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:31,550
I'll take care of that myself.

134
00:06:33,150 --> 00:06:35,583
But what was that?

135
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:37,583
"Warm?"

136
00:06:38,450 --> 00:06:39,883
That was...

137
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:43,250
The mung beans were warm when cooked,

138
00:06:43,250 --> 00:06:45,250
so the bindaetteok tasted especially good.

139
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:48,950
Eun Ae, Mom says to come eat quickly.

140
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:50,250
Come in, Team Manager.

141
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,250
Yes, I'm coming.

142
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:57,250
This is nuts! Seriously!

143
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:02,750
I never imagined he'd leave so quickly.

144
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:06,883
Do you know where Gyeol went?

145
00:07:07,383 --> 00:07:09,950
No.
He just said he was looking for a place,

146
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,250
so I had no idea
he'd leave right away either.

147
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:15,750
Ask him where he's staying
when you get to work.

148
00:07:16,150 --> 00:07:18,150
I want to send him
some side dishes at least.

149
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:19,650
Yes, I will, Grandma.

150
00:07:19,750 --> 00:07:23,250
Mother, there are restaurants everywhere.

151
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:25,883
All you have to do is tap your phone,

152
00:07:25,883 --> 00:07:27,650
and food gets delivered
right to your door.

153
00:07:27,983 --> 00:07:29,983
Why worry so much?

154
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:33,550
At least pretend to worry like a mother.

155
00:07:34,450 --> 00:07:36,450
How can you be so detached,
like you're talking about a stranger?

156
00:07:36,850 --> 00:07:38,883
Did I force him out of the house?

157
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:41,750
He left because he wanted to.
Why are you blaming me?

158
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:46,183
Please don't worry too much.

159
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:49,083
He's not some little kid anymore.

160
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:51,083
Eat, Father.

161
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:57,150
What's wrong? Is your appetite off?

162
00:07:58,083 --> 00:07:59,683
Then I'll make you some porridge.

163
00:07:59,683 --> 00:08:00,750
No, it's fine.

164
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:05,050
I'll just mix some rice into the soup.

165
00:08:09,183 --> 00:08:11,450
So refreshing. It really clears me up,

166
00:08:12,250 --> 00:08:13,683
even though I didn't drink last night.

167
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,283
What?

168
00:08:18,650 --> 00:08:21,750
Mother, about the couples' gathering...

169
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:23,250
Have you decided on the menu?

170
00:08:24,950 --> 00:08:27,650
I made a list based on a famous...

171
00:08:27,650 --> 00:08:29,450
Korean set meal restaurant's menu.

172
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:30,783
If that's the case, just eat out.

173
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:33,950
I thought
it was just going to be a simple meal.

174
00:08:34,350 --> 00:08:35,850
But what? You think she's a cook?

175
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:40,050
I'll take care of it, so don't get upset.

176
00:08:40,283 --> 00:08:42,650
Of course.

177
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:44,450
Just keep it simple,
the way you want, Mother.

178
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:46,383
Please.

179
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,650
I'm sorry, Father, Mother.

180
00:08:51,183 --> 00:08:52,250
Thank you.

181
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:56,650
Don't you think Mother's voice
has been getting louder these days?

182
00:08:57,350 --> 00:09:00,383
It's like the deer's playing king
in a cave without a tiger.

183
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:04,550
The saying is about a fox, not a deer.

184
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:06,250
Whether it's a deer or a fox...

185
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,550
Well, Crystal...

186
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:10,950
When you want
to act like you know something,

187
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:12,850
at least try looking it up first.

188
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:14,450
Everything else about you is fine...

189
00:09:15,450 --> 00:09:17,350
Yeah, I'm ignorant. So what?

190
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:19,583
What do you mean, "so what?"

191
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,850
Whether you're ignorant or knowledgeable,

192
00:09:21,850 --> 00:09:25,183
I just love my Crystal so much
I could die.

193
00:09:26,183 --> 00:09:27,583
Are you seriously joking right now?

194
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:30,450
With the shares Father left her,

195
00:09:30,450 --> 00:09:31,983
she's already acting all high and mighty.

196
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:35,050
And if the daughter Mr. Seo is looking for
shows up,

197
00:09:35,483 --> 00:09:38,383
you and I will be broke. Completely broke.

198
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:40,650
Broke.

199
00:09:42,050 --> 00:09:43,450
Hey, I'm allergic to being broke.

200
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:53,383
Get off here.

201
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,950
What? Here?

202
00:09:55,350 --> 00:09:57,083
Were you planning to ride all the way
to the office with me?

203
00:09:59,983 --> 00:10:01,850
Because you're worried
people might see us come in together,

204
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:03,650
you want me to get off here? Here.

205
00:10:04,650 --> 00:10:06,083
Fine, whatever.

206
00:10:06,850 --> 00:10:10,150
Like I said, don't let it show, got it?

207
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,150
Good morning.

208
00:10:23,150 --> 00:10:24,783
- Good morning, Team Manager.
- Yes.

209
00:10:24,783 --> 00:10:25,983
- Hello.
- Yes.

210
00:10:25,983 --> 00:10:29,083
Hello, Team Manager.
You're a bit late today.

211
00:10:29,083 --> 00:10:31,583
Yes, someone dropped me off
very far from the office...

212
00:10:31,583 --> 00:10:35,483
Team Manager, what time
should we start the meeting today?

213
00:10:35,483 --> 00:10:37,450
Let me catch my breath first.

214
00:10:38,850 --> 00:10:40,350
These are documents from General Affairs.

215
00:10:40,350 --> 00:10:42,550
Please submit any requests you have.

216
00:10:42,583 --> 00:10:43,650
Yes, understood.

217
00:10:44,450 --> 00:10:46,383
Team Manager,
what perfume are you wearing?

218
00:10:46,483 --> 00:10:47,750
It smells really nice today...

219
00:10:49,683 --> 00:10:51,983
It smells like
the same perfume Ms. Cho Eun Ae uses.

220
00:10:52,483 --> 00:10:55,983
What?
I've never worn perfume in my life...

221
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:00,283
This is the shampoo I use.

222
00:11:00,850 --> 00:11:04,150
Really? I guess you use the same shampoo.

223
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:05,650
Yes, well...

224
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:16,583
Chief Ko and I have a meeting...

225
00:11:16,583 --> 00:11:17,950
with the Lucas Design Team,

226
00:11:17,950 --> 00:11:19,483
so let's have our team meeting
in the afternoon.

227
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:21,750
See you later.

228
00:11:22,083 --> 00:11:23,450
See you later, Manager Seo.

229
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:29,250
Where are you going so early?

230
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:32,150
To an investment briefing...

231
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:35,250
I'm meeting a junior.

232
00:11:35,350 --> 00:11:37,450
That junior from last time? Why?

233
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:39,750
Actually...

234
00:11:41,583 --> 00:11:43,183
Never mind. I'll tell you later.

235
00:11:43,750 --> 00:11:44,883
Bit Na, have a good day at kindergarten.

236
00:11:44,883 --> 00:11:45,883
Yes, Mom.

237
00:11:45,883 --> 00:11:46,883
You're such a cutie.

238
00:11:47,750 --> 00:11:49,450
- Have a good day, honey.
- Okay.

239
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:51,950
Dad, what's an investment?

240
00:11:52,150 --> 00:11:55,383
Mom said an investment briefing earlier.

241
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:58,050
To explain it simply,

242
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:00,650
you hand over one apple...

243
00:12:01,450 --> 00:12:04,150
and get several in return.

244
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,550
So Mom went to hand over apples?

245
00:12:07,950 --> 00:12:10,950
I don't think so. We don't have any apples
to hand over right now.

246
00:12:11,450 --> 00:12:15,150
Sometimes, even if you hand over an apple,
you might not get anything back.

247
00:12:15,883 --> 00:12:17,750
So investment is risky.

248
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:21,650
It's not always like that,
but if you choose poorly, it can be risky.

249
00:12:22,483 --> 00:12:24,683
All done. You look so cute, Bit Na.

250
00:12:24,683 --> 00:12:25,750
- Shall we go?
- Yeah.

251
00:12:26,483 --> 00:12:27,483
Let's go.

252
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:36,483
So this is the studio we'll be sharing.

253
00:12:36,850 --> 00:12:38,450
Excuse me, are you moving in here?

254
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:39,983
Why do you have so much stuff?

255
00:12:43,150 --> 00:12:46,083
You'll see. They're all things I need.

256
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:51,083
I'll use this desk,
so you can use that one.

257
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:52,550
Sure.

258
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:01,583
Wait a second.

259
00:13:02,450 --> 00:13:04,283
Let's clean first.

260
00:13:28,650 --> 00:13:31,883
All right, all done.
Now unpack your stuff.

261
00:13:33,850 --> 00:13:36,750
From now on,
don't touch my desk without permission.

262
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:38,750
Sure, whatever you say.

263
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:42,750
These...

264
00:14:00,650 --> 00:14:01,650
Good?

265
00:14:08,150 --> 00:14:10,383
Why did they install the shelf so high?

266
00:14:11,583 --> 00:14:13,883
- Sit down for a moment.
- Okay.

267
00:14:18,183 --> 00:14:21,383
Even though we're collaborating,

268
00:14:21,983 --> 00:14:24,083
strictly speaking,
the novel is the original work, right?

269
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:27,283
Well, strictly speaking, yes.

270
00:14:27,683 --> 00:14:29,850
I handle the writing,
you handle the drawings.

271
00:14:30,283 --> 00:14:32,183
Let's stick to our own territory.

272
00:14:33,083 --> 00:14:35,283
So you're saying...

273
00:14:35,283 --> 00:14:37,383
I shouldn't give any opinions
on your novel,

274
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:39,750
and I should just draw whatever you write?

275
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,883
Something like that?

276
00:14:42,583 --> 00:14:44,650
Yes, I'll take that as you understood...

277
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:45,950
Then you, as the writer,

278
00:14:47,050 --> 00:14:49,750
won't comment on my drawings either.

279
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:53,083
"Comment?" No, I won't.

280
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,350
Hold it in.

281
00:14:59,150 --> 00:15:01,650
If it's for drawing "The ER Witch"...

282
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:19,483
On a day like today,

283
00:15:19,483 --> 00:15:21,750
I thought about what kind of comfort
I should give you,

284
00:15:22,383 --> 00:15:24,350
and how I could ease your heavy heart,

285
00:15:24,350 --> 00:15:27,183
but I just couldn't figure it out.

286
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:32,383
So I just prepared this
to show my support and encouragement.

287
00:15:32,383 --> 00:15:33,650
Please accept it
without feeling pressured.

288
00:15:41,050 --> 00:15:42,783
If we accept all of Lucas's suggestions,

289
00:15:42,783 --> 00:15:45,283
the initial cost will exceed expectations
by a lot.

290
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:47,450
You don't need to worry about that.

291
00:15:47,450 --> 00:15:48,583
I'll take full responsibility.

292
00:15:48,883 --> 00:15:50,650
It's not that simple.

293
00:15:57,550 --> 00:15:58,550
Yes, Team Manager.

294
00:15:58,550 --> 00:16:01,450
Hey, can you make some time after work?

295
00:16:03,250 --> 00:16:04,250
After work?

296
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:07,783
Yes, I can.

297
00:16:11,383 --> 00:16:13,650
- Was that Gyeol?
- That's my personal business.

298
00:16:13,650 --> 00:16:15,050
Right, personal.

299
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:18,883
Then I guess you're not curious
about his personal life either.

300
00:16:22,283 --> 00:16:24,550
- Gyeol moved out.
- What?

301
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:27,450
He asked me why I hadn't moved out yet
even though I'm all grown up.

302
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:29,450
Should I try living on my own too?

303
00:16:30,383 --> 00:16:32,350
Do you know where he moved to?

304
00:16:32,550 --> 00:16:35,650
No. He said he'd move out the other day
and left the next day.

305
00:16:36,183 --> 00:16:37,550
What is he, some goblin?

306
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,550
Right, this weekend,

307
00:16:40,550 --> 00:16:43,283
there's that couples' gathering
with the parents.

308
00:16:43,650 --> 00:16:45,250
Should we have a bonding event
that day too?

309
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:47,883
How about a housewarming at Gyeol's place?

310
00:16:48,350 --> 00:16:49,850
Do you really think that's possible?

311
00:16:49,850 --> 00:16:51,450
Nothing's impossible, right?

312
00:16:51,450 --> 00:16:52,883
How about I make it happen?

313
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,250
Arranging things is my specialty.

314
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,250
There she goes again. Wait for me.

315
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:07,883
Did you have a good lunch?

316
00:17:08,683 --> 00:17:11,083
Yes. Why did you skip yours?

317
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:12,750
I don't usually eat breakfast,

318
00:17:12,750 --> 00:17:14,950
but I overate at your place this morning.

319
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:17,150
Careful. Someone might hear you.

320
00:17:18,850 --> 00:17:20,650
Have this later as a snack.

321
00:17:21,650 --> 00:17:24,450
Are you worried because I skipped lunch?

322
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:26,050
Of course I am.

323
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:29,350
I believe in eating three meals a day,
no matter what.

324
00:17:30,183 --> 00:17:32,050
We work to eat, after all.

325
00:17:32,583 --> 00:17:33,850
If you're so worried about me,

326
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:35,950
why did you just leave me
on the street like that?

327
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:39,583
I didn't leave you!
I didn't want people to misunderstand.

328
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,683
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, do you think
you're some kind of celebrity?

329
00:17:42,950 --> 00:17:45,283
What? Why would I think that?

330
00:17:45,883 --> 00:17:49,550
People don't actually care about others
as much as you think.

331
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:50,950
You're just overthinking it.

332
00:17:51,683 --> 00:17:55,383
Anyway, find another place soon.

333
00:17:55,383 --> 00:17:57,250
Mind your own business.

334
00:17:58,983 --> 00:18:00,583
How are you getting home?

335
00:18:01,150 --> 00:18:02,750
Should we meet up where I dropped you off
this morning?

336
00:18:02,883 --> 00:18:05,683
No, I have plans tonight.
Go home on your own.

337
00:18:05,983 --> 00:18:08,950
What? Okay then.

338
00:18:10,883 --> 00:18:13,050
But what plans?

339
00:18:14,250 --> 00:18:15,250
Why?

340
00:18:15,650 --> 00:18:18,450
Are you interested in me by any chance?

341
00:18:18,983 --> 00:18:19,983
What?

342
00:18:20,783 --> 00:18:22,783
Are you delusional?

343
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:27,550
Who is this?

344
00:18:28,450 --> 00:18:30,083
Grandma, aren't those my clothes?

345
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:32,083
Yeah, the top is yours,

346
00:18:32,583 --> 00:18:36,150
and I bought the rest
at the market yesterday.

347
00:18:36,483 --> 00:18:37,483
How do I look?

348
00:18:39,150 --> 00:18:42,083
If I go out like this,
will it mask my age a bit?

349
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:44,483
There's no age limit for line dancing.

350
00:18:44,483 --> 00:18:46,283
But you do look ten years younger.

351
00:18:46,283 --> 00:18:48,650
I've always looked young.

352
00:18:48,650 --> 00:18:50,550
If I really dress up,

353
00:18:50,550 --> 00:18:52,450
people think I'm around 60.

354
00:18:52,483 --> 00:18:55,450
Come on, that's a bit much, Grandma.

355
00:18:55,450 --> 00:18:58,550
No, I could say she's my friend today
and people would believe it.

356
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,850
"Friend" might be pushing it.
Let's go now.

357
00:19:02,350 --> 00:19:06,450
I'm curious
what that smug woman looks like.

358
00:19:07,350 --> 00:19:08,350
Cho Rong, we'll be back.

359
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:11,150
- You've got this, Grandma!
- Yeah, I've got this.

360
00:19:12,950 --> 00:19:16,150
Then I should work
on improving the new three menu items.

361
00:19:18,250 --> 00:19:22,850
So this is the company
where Seong Jun and Eun Ae work?

362
00:19:23,883 --> 00:19:25,583
It's huge.

363
00:19:26,883 --> 00:19:30,150
That's where I caught him cleaning.

364
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:34,350
Let's go. We need to warm up first.

365
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:38,550
I watched something on YouTube...

366
00:19:38,550 --> 00:19:41,150
and learned the basic steps. Want to see?

367
00:19:44,983 --> 00:19:46,850
One, two, three, four.

368
00:19:46,850 --> 00:19:48,850
One, two, three, four.

369
00:19:48,850 --> 00:19:50,150
One, two, three...

370
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:15,950
- How is it?
- It's great.

371
00:20:15,950 --> 00:20:16,983
- Amazing.
- Yeah.

372
00:20:27,683 --> 00:20:29,950
Was I dreaming?

373
00:20:38,450 --> 00:20:39,983
Let's warm up first.

374
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:42,950
I'm dying.

375
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,383
Hello, Kang Yeon Ja.

376
00:20:46,850 --> 00:20:47,883
Hello.

377
00:20:58,683 --> 00:21:01,050
Who are you? This is my spot.

378
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:02,883
Do you see a name tag here?

379
00:21:03,350 --> 00:21:04,650
Come this way, Sun Bun.

380
00:21:04,650 --> 00:21:07,150
What? Do you know her?

381
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:11,350
Yes, she's my neighbor
who just signed up today.

382
00:21:11,450 --> 00:21:13,850
I see. Nice to meet you.

383
00:21:14,183 --> 00:21:15,350
I look forward to dancing with you.

384
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,783
There are all kinds of ways
to stir trouble.

385
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:20,750
Trouble?

386
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:23,550
What are you muttering about?

387
00:21:23,883 --> 00:21:25,650
Are you saying I'm stirring trouble here?

388
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:26,883
When did I ever?

389
00:21:27,450 --> 00:21:30,383
I just said I was thirsty
and needed some water.

390
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:33,383
So now you're saying I'm hard of hearing?

391
00:21:34,483 --> 00:21:36,283
When did I say that?

392
00:21:37,150 --> 00:21:38,883
Jeong Ran, say something.

393
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:40,883
I didn't say anything like that, right?

394
00:21:41,250 --> 00:21:44,483
What? I didn't hear. I was distracted.

395
00:21:52,450 --> 00:21:55,250
Back in my day, I could really talk tough.

396
00:21:56,483 --> 00:21:58,250
Want to go for a round?

397
00:22:00,250 --> 00:22:02,350
Come here.

398
00:22:03,450 --> 00:22:06,183
Hey, do something. I'm scared of her.

399
00:22:06,383 --> 00:22:08,450
Please stop. You're scaring her.

400
00:22:08,450 --> 00:22:09,450
Stop!

401
00:22:10,283 --> 00:22:12,650
You take the center spot. I'll give it up.

402
00:22:15,483 --> 00:22:16,483
Not respecting your elders...

403
00:22:20,850 --> 00:22:22,250
- Hello.
- Hello.

404
00:22:22,683 --> 00:22:23,683
Hello.

405
00:22:25,883 --> 00:22:27,950
All right, shall we begin?

406
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:29,050
- Yes.
- Yes.

407
00:22:33,850 --> 00:22:36,250
Ready, five, six, start.

408
00:23:01,650 --> 00:23:04,683
Mr. Ju,
you said you had something to tell me?

409
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:08,183
What? Right.

410
00:23:09,350 --> 00:23:12,250
So, how's that Dae Chi user manual
I gave you?

411
00:23:12,250 --> 00:23:13,383
Are you using it well?

412
00:23:13,550 --> 00:23:15,683
Sorry? Yes.

413
00:23:16,350 --> 00:23:18,783
Treat it like a textbook.

414
00:23:18,783 --> 00:23:20,750
Read it again and again, okay?

415
00:23:20,750 --> 00:23:22,350
Memorize it thoroughly.

416
00:23:22,750 --> 00:23:23,750
Understood.

417
00:23:24,450 --> 00:23:28,183
By any chance, do you have anything to say
about the Finance Director?

418
00:23:30,583 --> 00:23:32,050
The Finance Director? Why?

419
00:23:32,683 --> 00:23:34,883
He seems quite close to the CEO,

420
00:23:35,283 --> 00:23:37,283
so I was wondering
if there's anything I should keep in mind.

421
00:23:39,550 --> 00:23:41,550
Mr. Cho,

422
00:23:41,883 --> 00:23:45,883
this is some sincere advice from a senior.

423
00:23:46,583 --> 00:23:48,050
Don't dig too deep.

424
00:23:48,883 --> 00:23:51,950
Do just enough, okay? Just enough.

425
00:23:52,750 --> 00:23:55,883
What? Is there any reason...

426
00:23:58,550 --> 00:24:01,783
Mr. Seo, the Chairman doesn't call you
to the house these days?

427
00:24:02,350 --> 00:24:05,350
No, there's a lot to handle at the office.

428
00:24:05,683 --> 00:24:08,250
So, what do you think?

429
00:24:08,583 --> 00:24:11,983
Doesn't Mr. Cho seem like
he'll soon surpass me...

430
00:24:11,983 --> 00:24:14,050
and become a truly professional assistant?

431
00:24:14,850 --> 00:24:15,883
You flatter me.

432
00:24:19,450 --> 00:24:20,850
What is this? Yong Man.

433
00:24:21,783 --> 00:24:24,283
You left the company ages ago.
Why are you still in here?

434
00:24:24,883 --> 00:24:26,850
And if you came,
shouldn't you see me first?

435
00:24:27,350 --> 00:24:28,350
Why should I?

436
00:24:31,983 --> 00:24:33,050
Remember this.

437
00:24:33,450 --> 00:24:35,850
Whatever it is, just keep it moderate.

438
00:24:38,150 --> 00:24:41,250
I'll take my leave now.
Good work, everyone.

439
00:24:41,683 --> 00:24:43,550
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye, take care.

440
00:24:46,950 --> 00:24:49,150
Yes, Chairman. Understood.

441
00:24:56,383 --> 00:24:59,283
But what were the three of you
talking about?

442
00:25:00,350 --> 00:25:02,983
Were you plotting something
when I walked in?

443
00:25:03,350 --> 00:25:04,583
Plotting?

444
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:09,550
I need to request some supplies,
so I'll stop by General Affairs.

445
00:25:13,250 --> 00:25:16,450
What? Am I being left out?

446
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:20,350
I'll clock out first.

447
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:21,950
Yes, good work.

448
00:25:22,550 --> 00:25:23,950
- Yes, see you...
- Excuse me.

449
00:25:23,950 --> 00:25:25,083
See you tomorrow, Team Manager.

450
00:25:30,183 --> 00:25:32,083
Shall we eat first?
Where do you want to go?

451
00:25:32,850 --> 00:25:34,850
I'm fine with anything. Whatever you want.

452
00:25:41,750 --> 00:25:44,850
Do you remember the last time
you visited me in the army?

453
00:25:46,050 --> 00:25:47,250
How could I forget?

454
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,750
That was the day I confessed
and got completely rejected.

455
00:25:51,983 --> 00:25:54,650
When I said if it kept going like that,
we couldn't see each other anymore,

456
00:25:55,650 --> 00:25:58,850
I said that
because I didn't want to lose you.

457
00:26:01,850 --> 00:26:02,950
What do you mean?

458
00:26:03,450 --> 00:26:06,550
You rejected me
because you didn't want to lose me?

459
00:26:08,383 --> 00:26:09,383
Back then,

460
00:26:10,650 --> 00:26:13,250
I didn't want to fully open my heart
to anyone.

461
00:26:15,350 --> 00:26:19,250
Because if I liked and loved someone
and lost them,

462
00:26:19,983 --> 00:26:22,083
everything in my life
would completely fall apart.

463
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:24,850
I realized that too early.

464
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:30,450
That was then. What about now?

465
00:26:32,183 --> 00:26:33,850
Even now, I don't want to lose you.

466
00:26:34,450 --> 00:26:36,250
That's how important you are to me.

467
00:26:37,350 --> 00:26:40,850
I don't want you to get hurt
because of me.

468
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:43,450
Then just accept my feelings.

469
00:26:44,350 --> 00:26:46,350
Just open your heart to me.

470
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:53,750
Seung Ri, I'm sorry, but...

471
00:26:56,583 --> 00:26:57,783
there's someone I like.

472
00:27:22,983 --> 00:27:25,850
(Our Happy Days)

473
00:27:25,883 --> 00:27:28,483
Mom, Dad,
Team Manager will be moving out soon.

474
00:27:28,483 --> 00:27:30,350
No, I have absolutely no intention
of moving out.

475
00:27:30,883 --> 00:27:32,450
The Housing Lease Protection Act...

476
00:27:32,450 --> 00:27:33,650
Forget the law.

477
00:27:33,650 --> 00:27:35,883
I know.
You're just pretending to like him...

478
00:27:35,883 --> 00:27:37,350
to make me jealous.

479
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:38,650
Hey, Mr. Han Ji Hun.

480
00:27:38,650 --> 00:27:41,450
You've been out of my life
for a long time already.

481
00:27:41,450 --> 00:27:45,150
Love comes back around!

482
00:27:45,150 --> 00:27:46,950
Once Seong Jun joins too,

483
00:27:46,950 --> 00:27:48,783
the three of you
will have a lot to talk about.

484
00:27:49,850 --> 00:27:50,850
They must be here.

485
00:27:50,850 --> 00:27:52,550
That top-of-the-class janitor friend
and his wife.

486
00:27:52,950 --> 00:27:54,350
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
